==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: fledgling
<hw>fledgling</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a
new member of a group.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> newcomer, fledgeling, starter, neophyte, freshman,
entrant.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A young bird just fledged.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fledgling</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: fledgling
<hw>fledgling</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having just acquired
its flight feathers; -- of a young bird; <as>as, a <ex>fledgling</ex>
robin</as>.</def> <mark>[prenominal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fledgeling(prenominal).</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>young and inexperienced; <as>as, a
<ex>fledgling</ex> enterprise; a <ex>fledgling</ex>
skier</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unfledged.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flee</ent>⟦br⟧
